The paper focuses on the human-in-the-loop process of ensuring fairness in machine learning systems, which involves both human-computer interaction (HCI) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Therefore, cs.HC is the most likely category. The paper also discusses different types of explanations and their impact on fairness judgments, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential security and privacy implications of machine learning systems, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) or cryptography (cs.CR).
